OL,3,CNigerian chess champion breaks
OL,4,Cmarathon record by playing for 60 hours
OL,6,FOnakoya took to X, formerly known as
OL,7,FTwitter, to announce his intention to
OL,8,Fplay for longer, saying, "We're
OL,9,Fpushing to 60 hours, guys. We're not
OL,10,Fstopping yet. Let's keep going.
OL,12,F"We have a fundraising goal to meet
OL,13,Ffor the education of African children
OL,14,Faround the world.
OL,16,F"This is our why - the reason we are
OL,17,Fdoing this."
