OL,3,CNigerian chess champion breaks
OL,4,Cmarathon record by playing for 60 hours
OL,6,FChess in Slums Africa, the charity
OL,7,FOnakoya founded in 2018, aims to help
OL,8,Feducate one million children in slum
OL,9,Fcommunities across the continent.
OL,11,FOnakoya played against Shawn Martinez,
OL,12,Fa US chess champion, in accordance
OL,13,Fwith the Guinness World Record
OL,14,Fguidelines that any attempt to break
OL,15,Fthe record must be made by two players
OL,16,Fwho play continuously for the duration.
OL,18,FFueled by Nigerian jollof rice,
OL,19,FAfrobeats music and messages of
OL,20,Fsupport from across the globe, Onakoya
OL,21,Fwon every game against Martinez.
