OL,3,CNigerian chess champion breaks
OL,4,Cmarathon record by playing for 60 hours
OL,6,FThe match drew significant attention
OL,7,Fin Nigeria and was broadcast across
OL,8,Fmultiple locations in Lagos, the
OL,9,Fcountry's largest city, featuring
OL,10,Fwatch parties and digital billboards.
OL,12,FOnakoya founded Chess in Slums Africa,
OL,13,Fwhich seeks to empower children in
OL,14,Funderprivileged communities by using
OL,15,Fchess to enhance critical thinking and
OL,16,Fproblem-solving skills, in Lagos.
